Pickled Avocado

(use unripe avocados)

#1
1/2 c apple cider vinegar
1/2 c water
1/4 c honey
1 tsp whole allspice
1 tbsp salt

#2
1/2 c white vinegar
1/2 c water
1/4 c sugar
2 dill sprigs
1 bay leaf
1 tsp mustard seeds
1 tbsp salt

#3
1/2 c rice vinegar
1/2 c water
1/4 c sugar
1 tsp whole peppercorns
2-3 whole dried chiles
1 tbsp salt

Add brine ingredients in a small saucepan and bring to a boil. Once the sugar or honey dissolves, let the mixture cool to room temp, then pour over the avocado in a small jar and let sit for 2hrs before using.
#1 is good for chopped salads and salsas
#2 use like dill pickle (for sandwiches)
#3 cubed on crackers for appetizer
